This paper deals with the application of deep learning-based semantic segmentation in frames of surgery videos, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) domains. The paper also mentions the use of data augmentation techniques, which is a common topic in multimedia (cs.MM) research. Additionally, the paper involves the modification of a neural network architecture, which is a topic in both machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research.
